TASK 1: Replace Hardcoded Names with Dynamic Store Data
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Problem:
  Several files had patient/doctor names hardcoded instead of loading
  them dynamically from the store. This caused the app to always display
  demo data regardless of the actual logged-in user.

Fixes (7 locations across 5 files):

  ┌───┬────────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ # │ File : Line                        │ Change                             │
  ├───┼────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ 1 │ patient/clinic-checkin.tsx:177      │ "Sarah Johnson"                    │
  │   │                                    │ → patientName (loaded from store)   │
  ├───┼────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ 2 │ patient/treatment-complete.tsx:92   │ "Sarah Johnson"                    │
  │   │                                    │ → patientName (loaded from store)   │
  ├───┼────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ 3 │ doctor/patient-info.tsx:192-193     │ "Dr. Kim Minjun"                   │
  │   │                                    │ → doctorProfile?.name || "Doctor"   │
  │   │                                    │ "Seoul Bright Dental"               │
  │   │                                    │ → doctorProfile?.clinic || "Clinic" │
  ├───┼────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ 4 │ doctor/profile.tsx:33-46           │ Hardcoded full fallback profile     │
  │   │                                    │ → store.getDoctorProfile()          │
  ├───┼────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ 5 │ doctor/final-invoice.tsx:339+336   │ "Sarah Johnson" + "S" initial       │
  │   │                                    │ → casePatientName (from case data)  │
  ├───┼────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ 6 │ doctor/case-detail.tsx:104         │ "Dr. Kim Minjun" fallback           │
  │   │                                    │ → profile?.name || "Doctor"         │
  ├───┼────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ 7 │ doctor/case-detail.tsx:183-184     │ "Dr. Kim Minjun" + "Seoul Bright"   │
  │   │                                    │ → doctorProfile?.name/clinic        │
  └───┴────────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────┘

  Additional state variables added:
  - clinic-checkin.tsx: `patientName` state, loaded from getCurrentUser/getPatientProfile
  - treatment-complete.tsx: `patientName` state, loaded from getCurrentUser/getPatientProfile
  - patient-info.tsx: `doctorProfile` state, loaded from getDoctorProfile
  - final-invoice.tsx: `casePatientName` state, loaded from store.getCase()

  Verification: grep "Sarah Johnson|Dr. Kim Minjun|Seoul Bright" app/ → 0 results

Status: DONE


TASK 2: Improve `any` Types with Proper TypeScript Types
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Problem:
  Multiple useState hooks used `any` or `any[]` when proper interfaces
  were already exported from lib/store.ts.

Fixes:

  a) DentistQuote interface extended (lib/store.ts):
     Added optional fields used in quote-detail.tsx:
     + clinicPhotos?: string[]
     + yearsExperience?: number
     + specialties?: string[]

  b) State typing improvements:
     ┌──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────┬─────────────────────────┐
     │ File                         │ Before               │ After                   │
     ├──────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┤
     │ patient/quotes.tsx           │ useState<any[]>      │ useState<DentistQuote[]> │
     │ patient/quote-detail.tsx     │ useState<any>        │ useState<DentistQuote|null> │
     │ patient/payment.tsx          │ useState<any>        │ useState<DentistQuote|null> │
     └──────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────┴─────────────────────────┘

  c) Downstream `any` casts removed (quote-detail.tsx):
     - quotes.find((q: any) =>  →  quotes.find((q) =>
     - quote.treatments?.map((t: any, i: number) =>  →  .map((t, i) =>
     - quote.visits.map((v: any, idx: number) =>  →  .map((v, idx) =>

  d) Null safety fixes (quote-detail.tsx):
     - setQuote(found)  →  setQuote(found ?? null)
     - quote.visits.map  →  quote.visits!.map  (guarded by enclosing if)
     - v.paymentPercent > 0  →  (v.paymentPercent ?? 0) > 0
     - v.gapMonths > 0  →  (v.gapMonths ?? 0) > 0

Status: DONE


